---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="Full Service Automation — Formic"
  description="Formic's Full Service model covers equipment, software, service, and parts under one fixed monthly price. No CapEx. No surprise costs."
  ogTitle="Full Service Automation"
  ogDescription="Equipment, software, service, parts — one operator, one fixed price, every job on your floor."
>
  <link rel="canonical" href="https://formic.co/full-service" slot="head" />

<div class="detail-bc">
  <a href="/">Home</a><span class="sep">/</span>Full Service Automation
</div>

<section class="detail-hero">
  <div class="si">
    <div class="slabel" style="color:var(--orange)">Full Service Automation</div>
    <h1>Everything.<br><em>Included.</em></h1>
    <p class="lede">One fixed monthly price covers equipment, service, and technology. We scope your line, build the system, ship and install, and stay on it for life — your team never touches a robot integration project.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="detail-block white">
  <div class="db-grid">
    <div class="db-text">
      <div class="db-tag">01 — How It Works</div>
      <h2>From inquiry to <em>running production</em> in weeks.</h2>
      <p>The traditional automation model takes 12–18 months and millions in CapEx to deploy a single line. Formic compresses that into weeks with no capital risk — and stays on the line forever.</p>
      <ul class="feats">
        <li>Free application scoping and engineering review on your line</li>
        <li>Pre-engineered system designs deployed in days, not months</li>
        <li>Installation and commissioning by Formic engineers, not a third-party integrator</li>
        <li>Performance monitoring and SLAs from day one</li>
        <li>Continuous OTA upgrades — your system gets better, not older</li>
      </ul>
      <a href="/#cta" class="larr">Talk to an engineer →</a>
    </div>
    <div class="db-img"><img src="/Focus-7603.jpg" alt="Formic team scoping a customer line" loading="lazy"/><span class="img-cap">Scope · Build · Run</span></div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="detail-block lgrey">
  <div class="db-grid flip">
    <div class="db-img"><img src="/Talos-9787.jpg" alt="Formic engineer monitoring a fleet" loading="lazy"/><span class="img-cap">Cortex · Core · FPI</span></div>
    <div class="db-text">
      <div class="db-tag">02 — Software &amp; Technology</div>
      <h2>The intelligence behind <em>every system</em>.</h2>
      <p>Formic systems aren't just robots — they're connected, monitored, and continuously improved by software. Real-time visibility, remote diagnostics, and OTA updates mean every customer benefits from every deployment.</p>
      <ul class="feats">
        <li><strong>Cortex</strong> — software intelligence layer for fleet management and operator UX</li>
        <li><strong>Core</strong> — deterministic PLC control on industrial-grade hardware</li>
        <li>Real-time OEE, throughput, and cycle-time analytics, accessible to your team</li>
        <li>Encrypted remote diagnostics — most issues resolved without a site visit</li>
        <li>Backward-compatible feature releases across every deployed system</li>
      </ul>
      <a href="/magic" class="larr">Inside the platform →</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="detail-block white">
  <div class="db-grid">
    <div class="db-text">
      <div class="db-tag">03 — Equipment &amp; Flex</div>
      <h2>Modular hardware that <em>flexes with your line</em>.</h2>
      <p>Standardized "Lego-block" architecture means every Formic system shares the same modular building blocks. Easy to deploy, easy to maintain, easy to swap as your line evolves — without re-negotiating contracts or re-engineering cells.</p>
      <ul class="feats">
        <li>KUKA, ABB, FANUC, and Doosan robots — unified under one OS</li>
        <li>Swap or scale equipment without renegotiating your monthly agreement</li>
        <li>Backward-compatible upgrades across every deployment</li>
        <li>Field-tested designs deployed at scale — not custom one-offs</li>
        <li>Standardized spare-parts inventory across every site</li>
      </ul>
      <a href="/solutions" class="larr">See solutions →</a>
    </div>
    <div class="db-img"><img src="/Talos-0095.jpg" alt="Modular Formic equipment" loading="lazy"/><span class="img-cap">Modular · Flexible · Standardized</span></div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="detail-block dgrey">
  <div class="db-grid flip">
    <div class="db-img"><img src="/Talos-0143.jpg" alt="Formic field service engineer" loading="lazy"/><span class="img-cap">24/7 · Bilingual · SLA-backed</span></div>
    <div class="db-text">
      <div class="db-tag">04 — Service &amp; Parts</div>
      <h2>Keeping the system <em>running</em>.</h2>
      <p>Service is the whole job — that's why it's included, not invoiced. Bilingual 24/7 support, regional Field Service Engineers, contracted SLAs, and 100%-included maintenance. Parts are stocked, swaps are scheduled, downtime is engineered out.</p>
      <ul class="feats">
        <li>24/7 tech support — English and Spanish, every shift</li>
        <li>Regional Field Service Engineer network for rapid on-site response</li>
        <li>Performance SLAs written into every Full Service agreement</li>
        <li>Spare-parts inventory managed by Formic — no PO scrambles</li>
        <li>Predictive maintenance flagged before it becomes downtime</li>
      </ul>
      <a href="/#cta" class="larr">Get started →</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="detail-cta">
  <h2>No CapEx.<br>No Risk.<br>No Problems.</h2>
  <div class="btn-row">
    <a href="mailto:sales@formic.co" class="btn-ctadark">Get Started</a>
    <a href="/" class="btn-ctawh">Back to Home</a>
  </div>
</section>
</Layout>
